OL,6,FCheryl Littlefield is a Job Coach at
OL,7,Fthe factory. Her role, which supports
OL,8,Fstaff to help them shine, is paid for
OL,9,Fthrough Access to Work funding.
OL,11,FShe said: "If the factory were to
OL,12,Fclose, it would have a huge impact on
OL,13,Fall the guys who work here. They love
OL,14,Fworking here, they come in with a huge
OL,15,Fsmile on their face, we have a good
OL,16,Flaugh, there's good banter, and it's a
OL,17,Fvery relaxed atmosphere."
OL,19,F"To take all of that away from them
OL,20,Fwould really affect their wellbeing."
